ZCZC GE09
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 062300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND NE THROUGH THE CENTRAL
N SEA WITH A TROUGH OF LOW PRESSURE OVER GERMAN BIGHT AND WITH FRONTAL
TROUGHS IN THE FAR NW OF THE CULLERCOATS AREA. FRONTAL TROUGHS ARE THEN EXP
TO MOV E THROUGH THE AREA DURING MONDAY WITH PRESSURE THEN RE-BLDN IN THE
FAR NW. THE RIDGE IS THEN EXP TO TRANSFER E ACROSS THE AREA ON TUESDAY AHEAD
OF FURTHER FRONTAL TROUGHS MOV FM THE W. WEDNESDAY IS THEN LIKELY TO SEE
SIMILAR CONDITIONS WITH THESE FRONTAL TROUGHS TRANSFERRING E DURING THE
DAY. NO SIG WINDS EXP ON SUNDAY AND MONDAY. STRG TO GALE FORCE WINDS ARE
LIKELY TO REACH THE NW OF CULLERCOATS ON BY TUESDAY EVENING THESE FCST TO
TRANSFER E ACROSS THE N OF THE AREA OVERNIGHT AND THEN MOD FM THE W ON WEDNESDAY
